    • Constructor Detail

      • DialogEvent

        protected DialogEvent(@NonNull
                      java.lang.String eventCode,
                      @Nullable
                      java.lang.String eventId)
        Creates a dialog event with the given codes and id. This constructor defaults to a 0 millisecond delay for processing the event, which means these are processed immediately.
        Parameters:
        eventCode - The code for this event as expected by dialogue.
        eventId - An id for this event, generally used to cancel related events.

      • DialogEvent

        protected DialogEvent(@NonNull
                      java.lang.String eventCode,
                      @Nullable
                      java.lang.String eventId,
                      long delayMillis)
        Creates a dialog event with the given codes and id. Additionally, it explicitly sets the amount of time that the event should wait before being processed by dialogue.
        Parameters:
        eventCode - The code for this event as expected by dialogue.
        eventId - An id for this event, generally used to cancel related events.
        delayMillis - Delay in millis before the event will be processed by dialogue.
